enhanced_by.reason: The azimuth method relies on the compassPoint state to determine the direction. Setting the compassPoint is necessary before calling azimuth.
Both azimuth and word methods return directional information based on the compassPoint. Assertions for azimuth can be informed by the output of the word method.
Both azimuth and abbreviation methods return directional information based on the compassPoint. Assertions for azimuth can be informed by the output of the abbreviation method.
